verse.lines:
{lang-eng}O Jesus, Lord, with me abide;
I rest in Thee, whate’er betide;
Thy gracious smile is my reward;
I love, I love Thee, Lord!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I love Thee so I know not how
My transports to control;
Thy love is like a burning fire
Within my very soul.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}For Thou to me art all in all;
My honor and my wealth;
My heart’s desire, my body’s strength,
My soul’s eternal health.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O light in darkness, joy in grief,
O heaven’s life on earth;
Jesus, my love, my treasure, who
Can tell what Thou art worth?{/lang-eng}
